<TITLE> Shops to stay open Fri, Sat to 10pm for Ramadan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 17, (bdnews24.com)The prime minister has directed shops to remain open till 10pm on Fridays and Saturdays during the month of Ramadan. The decision was made Monday at a cabinet meeting. Shops will be closed by 8pm on the other five days of the week, Abul Kalam Azad, the prime minister's press secretary, told reporters after the meeting. It was also decided a report on huge telephone bill arrears owed by members of parliament would not be submitted in a regular cabinet meeting, Azad said. Repayment of the arrears by lawmakers has shown an increase recently, he said. Some 199 MPs amassed telephone bill arrears totalling Tk 9.12 core till 2001. Currently, 135 of the MPs owe approximately Tk 1.60 crore. Monday's cabinet meeting also approved the National Science and Technology Museum Act 2009, said Azad. A seven-member council of advisers will be formed under the act with a minister or state-minister at the helm, he said. The council will hold meetings over the next three years, he added. The act will come into force after the passage of the bill in parliament, the press secretary said. b
